<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-04-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-04-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="930" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d930">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Russell.</persName></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-04-20"><hi rend="italic">April 20,
                                1903</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 105.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose herewith six copies of the
                            protocol between the United States and Venezuela.</p>
                        <p>You will advise the Venezuelan Government that the United States
                            Government has named as its commissioner Mr. William E. Bainbridge, and
                            as its agent before the commission Mr. Robert C. Morris; also that the
                            United States Government has presented the request on its part to the
                            Queen of the Netherlands to name an umpire, pursuant to the
                            protocol.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>